 "\nWe also know that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "181ac590-0f4d-483c-8bef-9ec05048b676"],
 " is the hypotenuse. From this new triangle, we can define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "35d66ab8-df2f-4995-9cc2-1beddb3872c5"],
 " as a transformation of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "18878a20-dd3e-48d5-8ca1-dbc4025783a6"],
 " :\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f132eb92-a3e0-4556-91c7-8a348ada1dbf"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "70836d52-904f-450c-b41f-633c61f0c9df"],
 " - (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f7d00c2d-b8d7-4363-a26f-83e6ede1b192"],
 "*cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "97a11185-ef2c-4f7f-80dd-94363e7f588b"],
 "),",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3196bbf4-568b-4e27-b22b-b1d59c6a531e"],
 "*sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e396a10e-9aa4-432f-bbd7-6974e5ea68bf"],
 "))\n\nWhich can be written out in Wolfram Language as the following:"
}], "Text",
