Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Model V3 - Multi-Jointed Self-Balancing Tail", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992100591446735*^9, {3.9921621171812067`*^9, 3.992162125037558*^9}, {
   3.992419485360118*^9, 3.992419489242263*^9}, {3.9924272718363523`*^9, 
   3.992427277888801*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"93d1465b-ed50-421e-9e24-\
077e0f67b308"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We now have a single-jointed tail which can rotate freely to counterbalance \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1acaeb06-1717-4e3e-ba3b-8fb87db7fc3f"],
 ". However, once again, in nature, monkeys and mammals in general have \
multi-jointed tails ranging from 11 to 49 caudal vertebrae (bones). To \
simulate this, we need to compute an algorithm that can take any number of \
joints, a given segment length and weight, and a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b5da1eac-6ca5-459e-857f-cb812b0199f5"],
 ", and computes the angles of the vertebrae. \n\nTo do this, we need to \
redefine our naming system for our variables. Our system above has six \
points, each titled ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f11220db-5528-40e4-b7b1-ab3727f3427b"],
 ", but approaching adding more and more points as well as midpoints/center \
of masses computationally will get unnecessary and convoluted. Thus, for this \
final model, we will only name the pivot points with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a07840b-62d1-4cbf-8c24-a56b54ea56b7"],
 " system, and we will name midpoints/center of masses with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c27c6d69-5bc1-4334-bcf5-6f1c447a524b"],
 " system. Because the n applies for the tail and only the tail, but we still \
have pivots and center of masses elsewhere, we will name the origin and head \
points with these special exceptions:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "81739206-65a2-42a1-9495-88e5c4507fe3"],
 " - the origin\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1b6f197c-9565-4d2b-b894-eaede8a13027"],
 " - the pivot point of the head\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d2a068-6058-41c3-9397-01a752e3d7ed"],
 " - the point mass associated with the head.\n\nLet\[CloseCurlyQuote]s show \
an example of all of these rules in a diagram, in this case with 4 segments \
for the tail:\n(DIAGRAM)\n\nInitially, we can define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b985fce9-8bd8-406d-b55d-0bd4545f42a7"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "19d9b31c-a498-46cd-b7d8-553025532424"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "df8ee79c-5abb-486b-9e9e-1dc78e6395c3"],
 ", as we have defined them for the previous two models as well, just under \
different names.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0675c9cd-cd3c-4ca1-bfe4-b7210b6e7033"],
 " = (0,0)\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5649d583-f0f7-4363-b1d8-8b0a563ca8b6"],
 " =  (-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "676b70e6-32b7-4505-b143-9d5bd330b87a"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1cebb9b5-11fa-4b1f-981a-35c8c7a5c94e"],
 "), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6bd14965-7407-4abc-894f-8b51c7526d64"],
 " * cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0e549930-98d0-4eae-bc0b-5e68daf6c5b8"],
 "))\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c1bcc044-82fb-4995-8391-ba2c2b3ace22"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "85e10313-1829-4895-b120-413ab99a003b"],
 " - (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f2473f0a-b448-43f9-91db-189c21f4f347"],
 "*cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1d7c3cf4-c30f-44b9-aa5a-fc844feb965e"],
 "),",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "148cdd77-19a3-4688-922f-d73ceaa2a699"],
 "*sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "24e02a03-239a-4e64-b77a-8a005821b5fd"],
 "))\n\nLet\[CloseCurlyQuote]s define these constants in Wolfram Language as \
well as redefine ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e480a7ac-074b-408d-bc47-33d462a7bddf"],
 ":"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423682082191*^9}, {3.9924238705781116`*^9, 3.99242387668334*^9}, {
   3.992425049548092*^9, 3.992425057403997*^9}, {3.9924285994951973`*^9, 
   3.992428662570973*^9}, {3.992428850322914*^9, 3.992428908887649*^9}, {
   3.9924290185375557`*^9, 3.992429084659481*^9}, {3.992429220944626*^9, 
   3.9924292334484262`*^9}, {3.992429283904768*^9, 
   3.992429285229557*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bca5491a-498b-4f3b-80e7-\
f3f06318eb42"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"p0", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "=", " ", "60"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"pH", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "hHead"}], "*", 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"hHead", "*", 
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"mH", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"pH", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
      RowBox[{"dHead", "*", 
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"pH", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
      RowBox[{"dHead", "*", 
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}]}], "}"}]}], 
  ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924292597898397`*^9, 3.992429286400412*^9}, {
  3.9924396724006863`*^9, 3.992439672439506*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[275]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9e44fd8e-aa41-4933-8443-5909960710c6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For simplicity\[CloseCurlyQuote]s sake, we will always use the same \
constant for the length of each tail segment, even though that is not the \
case in nature. We can define a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1b948b50-865c-4e1c-bb65-09b690a8140a"],
 " and then computationally create a list of it as a constant using Wolfram \
Language\[CloseCurlyQuote]s ConstantArray function. This is shown as the \
following:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423682082191*^9}, {3.9924238705781116`*^9, 3.99242387668334*^9}, {
   3.992425049548092*^9, 3.992425057403997*^9}, {3.9924285994951973`*^9, 
   3.992428662570973*^9}, {3.992428850322914*^9, 3.992428908887649*^9}, {
   3.9924290185375557`*^9, 
   3.992429079281085*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7d0e7f8f-bd76-4117-8558-\
3e0b5c9a2d70"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "listOfDistances", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"dTailConst", " ", "=", " ", "1.5"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"listOfDistances", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{"dTailConst", ",", "numPoints"}], "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992428678606969*^9, 3.9924286850377417`*^9}, 
   3.99243906701337*^9, {3.9924396742747917`*^9, 3.992439675645851*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[279]:=",ExpressionUUID->"a71bd04c-8517-410d-9da3-58fb45d6060a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1.5`", ",", "1.5`", ",", "1.5`", ",", "1.5`"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992439067258312*^9, {3.992439679954447*^9, 3.992439681635742*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[281]=",ExpressionUUID->"a8a4c81a-a677-4f8d-a96a-af1fc78a917c"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With these points defined, we can begin computing. We know that each of \
these joints must rotate. In the previous Model V2, the single jointed \
rotating tail, we needed to define a new angle, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "162ac574-f09c-4666-a3e8-903c723ab2d2"],
 ", such that it could rotate. Because each n-numbered joint is rotating, we \
need n number of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7a09af86-a00f-49b3-95b6-011c87e7cbbc"],
 " angles, each one named appropriately as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"adj", " ", "n"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d742d8e2-afb4-4ee2-bc89-eb22d141f0ca"],
 ". In our four-joint scenario, we can define the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "74a96968-5828-4a73-972b-275d2b525326"],
 " angles as the following angles between segments:\n(DIAGRAM)\nThese ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aa176c8c-0455-408c-aba1-825e80d939f8"],
 " angles are useful for creating an unknown variable to solve for, however, \
that is their entire purpose for now. As the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "840e6213-ccb5-470c-8b89-84193cd25a05"],
 " values for now are purely symbolic and used to only be a value to solve \
for, we can create a list of placeholder variables of them using a specified \
number of joints, in this case, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s say 4 to match our \
diagram. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423682082191*^9}, {3.9924238705781116`*^9, 3.99242387668334*^9}, {
   3.992425049548092*^9, 3.992425057403997*^9}, {3.9924285994951973`*^9, 
   3.9924286600765676`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"69bd3c7f-195d-4ff8-928a-\
e9e8b823ae65"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"numPoints", " ", "=", " ", "4"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "thetaAdjVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "n", "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924250319804783`*^9, 3.992425065090556*^9}, 
   3.992439049294832*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[282]:=",ExpressionUUID->"42701554-20b5-466c-8e9c-acb71409dade"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "1", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "2", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "3", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "4", "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9924390496155443`*^9, {3.992439680014943*^9, 3.992439681695715*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[284]=",ExpressionUUID->"55a4e017-74c8-4b86-a926-c5987a06f903"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We need to now establish a formula for getting the coordinates of the next \
point in the tail using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0fcff175-351d-4b3b-9647-f9f781485ea4"],
 ". To do this for the single jointed tail prior we used trigonometry and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aaec2160-bd18-4cea-99c6-8a52bf8b1480"],
 ". This works for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "963a749d-52ab-4b2c-9d2c-7275f269fcec"],
 " but no other subsequent angles. Thus, due to this discrepancy, we will \
establish a new variable type, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b7744f05-b430-42c0-96bc-8453a727c7f7"],
 ". ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f301eea-bf64-4a6e-8dcb-8282013fb9de"],
 " is the angle of the triangle used to compute the next point of the line. \
In our single jointed tail, what is now called ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "861a19d5-684c-44eb-bef5-82f19e4f223e"],
 " had been computed as the following:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "205e1e57-ae49-4087-a426-471859bbdba2"],
 "  = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj1"], " ", "-", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"90", "+", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"edb90b1f-1d2d-4fcb-a658-47d441a16f17"],
 "\n\nWe can see this in the following diagram:\n(DIAGRAM)\nLet\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s now begin computing for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "37f9416d-eb72-447b-9a0b-84e92d420bde"],
 ". To do so, we can draw an imaginary straight line to create a 180\[Degree] \
angle, and then relate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cf2bc363-5e98-47a1-8402-b015db9ee26f"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7cf433e6-7904-4522-a9b7-e229a866adf5"],
 " to values we already know, creating a supplementary angle. This can be \
viewed in the diagram:\n(DIAGRAM)\nNotice how, proven by alternate interior \
angles, the supplementary angle is actually just ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a3b1b6f-0643-4c0e-aea4-0b4e35edeb9a"],
 ". This means that we can define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "393af169-2fd7-4f06-b1ab-c91f2fd6509d"],
 " as the following:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "79ff93f7-37bd-4df8-bd0e-cb0987d28e95"],
 "  = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"180", " ", "-", " ", "90", "+", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a97bfd0d-da9b-403b-a40b-9aade08e9492"],
 "\n\nWith ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9516513c-f1c0-493b-957c-a75b95c80c19"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f389a009-c596-46a2-9f97-de9962d6faed"],
 " defined, we can actually define ANY angle afterwards now. Let\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s view this with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "03d2376e-775c-460c-ad9c-82124f0e7b18"],
 " in the following diagram, drawing an imaginary circle around ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "87f864f3-71e6-43ec-ab09-27d7e0f4f868"],
 " to visualize a 360\[Degree] angle:\n(DIAGRAM)\nblah\nblah\nblah\nThus, we \
can define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b0cb9efa-46f7-4c35-8294-48e3160b8359"],
 " as:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e849c384-37dc-4fcc-b7f1-b84e7f8f6e67"],
 " = 360 - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aadaf96f-b7e7-4d93-ad4e-dacf57cdcc13"],
 " - (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "02d87644-61cd-4603-b19a-a61a812fc6ff"],
 " - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bb965a7a-6d6e-47e5-8a9a-2b91d81d9a4e"],
 ")\n\nWe will see a similar pattern when we define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "26afa2e0-fc0e-4375-978d-8d7c22048de0"],
 " using this diagram:\n(DIAGRAM)\nblah\nblah\nblah\nThus, following the same \
pattern as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1a1037ad-3f54-416d-82a8-f10c56c1d8f8"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "93dc3f71-1d98-42d2-beac-3580ca382b0f"],
 " can be defined as:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f4701a07-a618-46ad-aa76-804f0375ec15"],
 " = 360 - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3238a4e7-7b81-4fd6-a319-50482f27b4b4"],
 " - (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9d30da08-e042-4447-9f06-924b53b667b3"],
 " - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d534ff1d-62f6-44e4-b8b8-747173eef666"],
 ")\n\nWe start to see a pattern once angles are defined with 360\[Degree]. \
We could go on infinitely defining the next angle in the monkey\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tail, but instead of that, we will create a formula, and \
represent it computationally with code. The formula for any angle in the \
monkey\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tail is:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "202f91fb-b43e-40a9-8a18-17e3a2f4f3e6"],
 " = 360 - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"adj", " ", "n"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "235a9c39-95a0-4ebd-9dcb-37ae06eda4cc"],
 " - (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"adj", " ", "n"}], " ", "-", " ", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"834a1453-54bf-4cca-9b5d-b4416b2a3a0f"],
 " - ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"n", " ", "-", " ", "2"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "989fbaa1-d3a5-4d1c-902f-4f5d7042c40c"],
 "),  n \[GreaterEqual] 3\n\nLet\[CloseCurlyQuote]s implement these thee \
formulas, for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b192f8c1-379a-4851-b6f4-f15c7b366750"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bcf4b6fd-0ea1-48cc-b575-a0b5a6a02c6b"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "39e14ae0-3773-429c-bbd7-21d8f4bff045"],
 " computationally using the Table and Which functions in Wolfram to use \
recursion and loop based on the numPoints variable defined earlier. We need \
to define temporary new variables as well due to memory allocation."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924182846744537`*^9, 3.992418319051136*^9}, {
   3.992418350578918*^9, 3.992418412636354*^9}, {3.992418475915766*^9, 
   3.992418615624667*^9}, {3.992418649433734*^9, 3.992418668332036*^9}, {
   3.9924187075300007`*^9, 3.9924188824505053`*^9}, 3.992420983827877*^9, {
   3.99242117495825*^9, 3.992421174958345*^9}, {3.992421292418934*^9, 
   3.992421328360664*^9}, {3.992421403622285*^9, 3.9924214478462667`*^9}, {
   3.992421559880987*^9, 3.992421592079218*^9}, {3.992421688029912*^9, 
   3.992421741583941*^9}, {3.9924218192142973`*^9, 3.992421819214427*^9}, 
   3.99242203718818*^9, {3.9924222545826607`*^9, 3.992422277626573*^9}, {
   3.9924234221371117`*^9, 3.992423443997818*^9}, {3.992423536113207*^9, 
   3.992423709668187*^9}, {3.992423912735525*^9, 3.9924240099190397`*^9}, {
   3.992424201218629*^9, 3.992424279518812*^9}, {3.9924246340721703`*^9, 
   3.9924246672185497`*^9}, {3.992424914122141*^9, 3.9924249779777803`*^9}, {
   3.992425074963813*^9, 3.9924250787633753`*^9}, {3.9924260985017357`*^9, 
   3.992426122816869*^9}, {3.992426295421831*^9, 3.992426364079625*^9}, {
   3.9924264734863567`*^9, 3.9924265491572943`*^9}, {3.992426673894291*^9, 
   3.992426744439538*^9}, {3.992426837513113*^9, 
   3.992426855318568*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c9313fa5-24a3-4e0e-828b-\
67dd94bfa06b"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "thetaVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"doubleprev", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"90", "+", "thetaLean"}], ")"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"prev", "=", 
   RowBox[{"180", "-", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"thetaVars", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\n", "\t", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Which", "[", "\n", "\t", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"n", "==", "1"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"90", "+", "thetaLean"}], ")"}]}], ",", "\n", "\t", 
       RowBox[{"n", "==", "2"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"prev", "=", " ", 
         RowBox[{"180", "-", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
             RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], ";", 
        RowBox[{"180", "-", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], ",",
        "\n", "\t", 
       RowBox[{"n", ">=", "3"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"360", " ", "-", " ", 
         RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", 
             RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], 
          ")"}]}], ";", " ", 
        RowBox[{"prev", "=", 
         RowBox[{"360", " ", "-", " ", 
          RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
             RowBox[{"[", 
              RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], 
           ")"}]}]}], ";", " ", 
        RowBox[{"doubleprev", "=", "prev"}]}]}], "\n", "\t", "]"}], ",", "\n", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992426805286147*^9, 3.99242681081077*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[285]:=",ExpressionUUID->"8da86b89-6f96-4ad0-aafb-f5088e541da8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With all of our ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "461bb785-e67e-4ee8-9d9e-62739495a199"],
 " variables defined, we can now get all remaining ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2a8e91d1-e155-4cde-9981-b141df08206c"],
 " point variables via simple trigonometry, and setting up the right \
triangles as we did earlier. Each coordinate, or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f2cccd5d-d622-45a0-98bb-b9fb5f51a8e9"],
 ", will be a transformation from the last coordinate in the sequence. To do \
this, however, we must define ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d28336c8-5c6b-493b-938c-4def28b33065"],
 ". We will simply use the same formula we used above in the Model V2 that \
relates ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3f6fe2aa-cfcc-4f00-88da-b9e87c1ac976"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c22452ab-632c-4c4b-b836-1641fe54c989"],
 ", and  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "75b80260-1acb-4f75-99bc-fbe3b328d2a9"],
 ":\n(DIAGRAM)\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3da13ba1-c830-48b9-b667-a5342641fc34"],
 " = (-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3797bc63-5f64-46b5-af66-3a00950ee4ec"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8ee8b956-31ac-487c-bb04-cfcd74a1c020"],
 "), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8fc2608e-0e3d-4b81-9a9f-a188e00f4f55"],
 " * cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4cdfdc8d-5165-439e-9467-6e77969a93a7"],
 "))\n\nWith ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "228ad59d-470c-450e-80e7-efc2ba2dea84"],
 " defined, any given point ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a6dc1ac9-62e9-451e-a33e-a5adac90b753"],
 " can then be given as a transformation using the previous point ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b0c8c03a-7015-4892-8993-ffa109f3b8e6"],
 " and the corresponding ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a01b86b-fe85-4add-bd86-f1e495128d6b"],
 ". Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s examine this with the below diagram and formula:\n\
(DIAGRAM)\nIn this case, we know the the hypotenuse, always being the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c1aa72df-97b5-40b7-92bd-afe821b84e05"],
 " constant, and we know the angle, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "70a1c70d-85a3-4eb7-a114-32548340d739"],
 ". Thus, because right triangles are always made, we can define any given \
coordinate as the following:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["p", "n"], " "}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d56087-dcf2-4166-a2b6-90d3782d6d91"],
 "= ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["p", 
     RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], " "}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e047d7ac-dc26-4bc4-96fb-b368c0d3755f"],
 " + (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], " "}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "75927b7b-9882-48dd-ba86-8eeb07ffb01c"],
 " * cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "76f767e4-d854-43a0-a1ee-abd8e76c50f4"],
 "), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], " "}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2ab3ff41-e0a8-4c3d-8a3c-c497592dfcb9"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f09f418-3cc8-42ea-901f-aa1f16b0d655"],
 ")); n \[GreaterEqual] 1\n\nThis formula can be implemented in the Wolfram \
Language using Table and an empty variable \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]p\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] to keep track of the last known point. Note that we \
must add numPoints by 1 for the total number of points, as each joint has a \
start and endpoint, thus meaning that for example for 4 joints, there are 5 \
points:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99242681595566*^9, 3.9924268316542253`*^9}, {
  3.9924269672537317`*^9, 3.992426985349269*^9}, {3.992427058181831*^9, 
  3.992427196925643*^9}, {3.992427243838944*^9, 3.992427256946658*^9}, {
  3.9924283426062813`*^9, 3.9924283632840357`*^9}, {3.992428440914689*^9, 
  3.992428508029765*^9}, {3.9924285875910263`*^9, 3.992428592161234*^9}, {
  3.992428694607253*^9, 3.9924288026147327`*^9}, {3.992429547736376*^9, 
  3.992429584315475*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8a08613d-d5ee-4e6f-ae79-\
27aef7f0d3fa"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "pVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"p", ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"pVars", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\n", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Which", "[", "\n", "\t", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"n", "==", "1"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"p", "=", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"-", "hTail"}], "*", 
           RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
            RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
          RowBox[{"hTail", "*", 
           RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
            RowBox[{"thetaLean", " ", "Degree"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}], ",", 
       "\n", "\t", 
       RowBox[{"n", ">=", "2"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"p", "=", 
        RowBox[{"p", "+", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"listOfDistances", "[", 
             RowBox[{"[", 
              RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
            RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"thetaVars", "[", 
               RowBox[{"[", 
                RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], " ", "Degree"}], 
             "]"}]}], ",", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"listOfDistances", "[", 
             RowBox[{"[", 
              RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "*", 
            RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"thetaVars", "[", 
               RowBox[{"[", 
                RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], " ", "Degree"}], 
             "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}]}]}], "]"}], ",", "\n", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", 
       RowBox[{"numPoints", "+", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99242881265384*^9, 3.992428815441949*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[289]:=",ExpressionUUID->"6dd53025-e81a-4c78-8ae3-eff3d1a651c5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We now must move on to calculating the center of masses, which are actually \
very simple. Each center of mass is simply the midpoint between the endpoints \
of a joint. Thus, we can use the following formula knowing that there is n+1 \
total number of points:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["m", "n"], " "}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4dbcfe04-ba45-461f-a7c6-75c8da1861d0"],
 "=  midpoint(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "39cf403e-78b0-43c4-826c-583af187c2ea"],
 ",",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", 
    RowBox[{"n", "+", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6dee2370-b7c4-496e-82a0-b5216c5451d4"],
 ")\n\nBecause Wolfram has a built-in Midpoint function, this becomes \
incredibly easy to compute:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.99242681595566*^9, 3.9924268316542253`*^9}, {
  3.9924269672537317`*^9, 3.992426985349269*^9}, {3.992427058181831*^9, 
  3.992427196925643*^9}, {3.992427243838944*^9, 3.992427256946658*^9}, {
  3.9924283426062813`*^9, 3.9924283632840357`*^9}, {3.992428440914689*^9, 
  3.992428508029765*^9}, {3.9924285875910263`*^9, 3.992428592161234*^9}, {
  3.992428694607253*^9, 3.992428800596725*^9}, {3.992429431698173*^9, 
  3.992429448344366*^9}, {3.992429538396015*^9, 3.992429545007667*^9}, {
  3.9924295889379663`*^9, 
  3.99242969743328*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"92faa809-f46d-42e8-bff2-\
1125d17b6bd6"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "mVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"mVars", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\n", "\t", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Midpoint", "[", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"pVars", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"pVars", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", 
          RowBox[{"n", "+", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", "\n", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992429706480315*^9, 3.992429708289136*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[292]:=",ExpressionUUID->"ced8c208-6af5-42ef-833b-582d4c994126"],

Cell["\<\
With all of our center of masses defined, we can now set up the torque \
equilibrium equation from our past two models. Before doing that, however, we \
must define our mass. Mass is a similar constant to distance, in that in real \
tails, it changes between joints, but for simplicity\[CloseCurlyQuote]s sake, \
we will define it as a single constant and use Wolfram to create a \
ConstantArray:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924297840613823`*^9, 3.992429835642281*^9}, {
  3.992429979252898*^9, 3.992429986050687*^9}, {3.9924300328885393`*^9, 
  3.992430126788211*^9}, {3.992430162063816*^9, 
  3.9924301819042253`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b10560b0-50db-4891-8d60-\
91eed27ac7c4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "listOfMasses", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"mTailConst", " ", "=", " ", "1"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"listOfMasses", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{"mTailConst", ",", "numPoints"}], "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992430201586566*^9, 3.992430203436946*^9}, 
   3.9924390585182323`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[294]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9b32c561-b702-4069-909b-3d19e35bc2d9"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1", ",", "1", ",", "1", ",", "1"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992439058785111*^9, {3.99243968046132*^9, 3.992439682144813*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[296]=",ExpressionUUID->"a6d1cefe-d28b-4c8f-9898-634e01bf8747"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We need to slightly tweak it from the previous two models, however, because \
our tail now has multiple joints. The torque on the tail now is a summation \
of the torque of every individual joint of the tail. This can be represented \
by the following:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Sum]", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ac03102-42f6-4cf8-b993-eb804d318a33"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d1dc23f5-3a7b-49d2-9fbb-279a5e347733"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "191fed6e-52d2-4adf-9b05-1858828d13ce"],
 ".x * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "26a6a5b7-5cc3-4908-bb98-501b89b8cb29"],
 " + ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "a1bbd2fb-1cc4-4e06-8349-401ebde0e654"],
 ".x * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "65864962-9b98-4281-9908-0b2fb2a42e6c"],
 " + ... +  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "n"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d5d7a636-ea7c-43fc-9ad9-414aa401b6a5"],
 ".x * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "003be000-b07e-403c-8dd1-5251cf8214ee"],
 "\n\nWe can represent this in Wolfram Language by creating a list for each \
torque, and then summing them up using the Total function:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9924297840613823`*^9, 3.992429835642281*^9}, {
  3.992429979252898*^9, 3.992429986050687*^9}, {3.9924300328885393`*^9, 
  3.992430126788211*^9}, {3.992430162063816*^9, 3.992430178918331*^9}, {
  3.992430333248941*^9, 3.9924303736643457`*^9}, {3.992430412941063*^9, 
  3.992430481540447*^9}, {3.992430522211628*^9, 
  3.992430532630219*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4908bd9d-ded6-468a-a7f5-\
1e87853dc679"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "torqueVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"torqueVars", "=", 
    RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\n", "\t", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"mVars", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], " ", "*", " ", 
       RowBox[{"listOfMasses", "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", "\n", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Total", "[", "torqueVars", "]"}], ";"}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992430537815002*^9, 3.992430544191409*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[297]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0675cfe7-9a33-447e-b4e0-9963397580da"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now, to create the equilibrium, we can add this total torque to the torque \
on the head, and set it equal to zero:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "fe94666c-be91-4268-bd7e-5277bb8c3eef"],
 " + ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Sum]", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "5ee25c68-5e31-4e80-873d-f56b57fb4afa"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "c5b90822-b7ff-4b70-b451-2ef9c790b2a5"],
 " = 0\n\nNow, just like the previous NSolve functions in Wolfram for the \
previous two models, we need to compute each of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1012da48-030e-4230-8dc9-e76ba367fd63"],
 " values. Before computing the values, we must define constraints such that \
all of the joints do not fold on each other. In the previous V2, we only \
defined the constraints as 0 to 180, however, here, we must be stricter and \
stick closer to 180 so the joints form a gradual and natural curve."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992430546160564*^9, 3.992430574793579*^9}, {
  3.992430647446924*^9, 3.992430686038555*^9}, {3.9924307408162403`*^9, 
  3.992430754278891*^9}, {3.9924385025856943`*^9, 3.992438584663288*^9}, {
  3.992438640573579*^9, 3.992438675778263*^9}, {3.9924389067790003`*^9, 
  3.9924389453976717`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"70070d21-4f0e-4f68-aa3d-\
a1e3cad045f7"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"lowerBound", "=", "160"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"upperBound", " ", "=", " ", "200"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"constraints", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"lowerBound", " ", "<=", " ", 
     RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "n", "]"}], " ", "<=", " ", "upperBound"}], ",",
     " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"n", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], 
   "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992439038272984*^9, {3.992439138154262*^9, 3.9924391412218847`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[300]:=",ExpressionUUID->"6220499a-0952-4ec5-a040-0faf47e57c3e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"160", "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "1", "]"}], "\[LessEqual]", "200"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"160", "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "2", "]"}], "\[LessEqual]", "200"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"160", "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "3", "]"}], "\[LessEqual]", "200"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"160", "\[LessEqual]", 
    RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "4", "]"}], "\[LessEqual]", "200"}]}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992439141512145*^9, {3.9924396805567617`*^9, 3.9924396822340107`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[302]=",ExpressionUUID->"ce6d151e-e1be-40bf-b862-5e66097cd5e5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Another change is that because there is n given solutions at any time, \
however, NSolve will not work due to its syntax requiring a system of \
equations with n amount of equations and n variables being solved for. As a \
result, we will use NMinimize and try to minimize the sum of the torques. \n\n\
NMinimize does this by finding the values which make the objective, the sum \
of the torques in this case, closest to zero. This will output an error value \
and each of the magnitudes for the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b01071b5-f5dc-4111-8abc-f8ac232e2ed6"],
 " values. When the error is anything above a near-zero value, we can assume \
that it is unsolvable anymore. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s define our objective as \
the sum of the torques and show the NSolve output below:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992438950260206*^9, 3.992439027179831*^9}, {
  3.992439695229824*^9, 
  3.992439748434547*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4bdee60c-7996-47b0-b175-\
3a04a1427c22"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"objective", " ", "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"torqueAtPoint", "[", 
        RowBox[{"mHead", ",", "mH"}], "]"}], " ", "+", " ", 
       RowBox[{"Total", "[", "torqueVars", "]"}]}], ")"}], "^", "2"}]}], 
   ";"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"output", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"NMinimize", "[", "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"objective", ",", " ", "constraints"}], "}"}], ",", 
    "thetaAdjVars"}], "\n", "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992439015782524*^9, 3.992439028276684*^9}, {
  3.992439149208548*^9, 3.992439152034925*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[303]:=",ExpressionUUID->"320d8e75-1d53-431a-97a4-cff83cc2e732"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"4.883243854824027`*^-16", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "1", "]"}], "\[Rule]", "194.5800181525595`"}], 
     ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "2", "]"}], "\[Rule]", "169.22448492369804`"}],
      ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "3", "]"}], "\[Rule]", "196.38048723978918`"}],
      ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdj", "[", "4", "]"}], "\[Rule]", 
      "176.54354662010445`"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9924391528688593`*^9, {3.992439680667101*^9, 3.9924396823241568`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[304]=",ExpressionUUID->"da917440-d468-47e9-9ead-39f8c59d56ce"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With each of our ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "79e71213-1db9-4cf5-a476-80f0279d83de"],
 " values defined, we can plug it back into our symbolic expressions and view \
the outputs by reassigning the physical values from output into the symbolic \
values of thetaAdjVars, and recompute our ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Theta]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "52eb6a72-23fb-48e0-b2c5-bd6a071c727d"],
 " and p values which relied on our ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "adj"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "840306b2-9f8b-4073-807a-449a655c62de"],
 " values:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992439229258428*^9, 3.992439298651322*^9}, {
  3.9924393352078667`*^9, 
  3.992439353840773*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c6cfdd2e-55a4-4c7d-a565-\
e4d4935db797"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Values", "[", 
   RowBox[{"output", "[", 
    RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.99243930001608*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[305]:=",ExpressionUUID->"67a4abe2-7fc4-4219-834d-0f5f19c2e99d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "194.5800181525595`", ",", "169.22448492369804`", ",", 
   "196.38048723978918`", ",", "176.54354662010445`"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.992439300903157*^9, {3.992439680727985*^9, 3.992439682383119*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[305]=",ExpressionUUID->"89f1424e-0014-4b1a-b194-9add4ccf0659"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "thetaVars", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"doubleprev", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
     RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"90", "+", "thetaLean"}], ")"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"prev", "=", 
   RowBox[{"180", "-", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"thetaVars", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Which", "[", "\n", "\t", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"n", "==", "1"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"90", "+", "thetaLean"}], ")"}]}], ",", "\n", "\t", 
      RowBox[{"n", "==", "2"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"prev", "=", " ", 
        RowBox[{"180", "-", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], ";", 
       RowBox[{"180", "-", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], ")"}]}]}], ",",
       "\n", "\t", 
      RowBox[{"n", ">=", "3"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"360", " ", "-", " ", 
        RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", 
            RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], 
         ")"}]}], ";", " ", 
       RowBox[{"prev", "=", 
        RowBox[{"360", " ", "-", " ", 
         RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "n", "]"}], "]"}], "-", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"thetaAdjVars", "[", 
            RowBox[{"[", 
             RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "-", "doubleprev"}], 
          ")"}]}]}], ";", " ", 
       RowBox[{"doubleprev", "=", "prev"}]}]}], "\n", "\t", "]"}], ",", "\n", 
    
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "numPoints"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9924393186122637`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[306]:=",ExpressionUUID->"6e221671-4d8b-4ae4-b4fb-c8d72ff461a8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "44.58001815255949`", ",", "55.35553322886145`", ",", "38.97504598907227`", 
